race.comment: SHEZA ALIBI (4) goes on top. She did some good things in Queensland over the Winter and her return in the Gothic Stakes was excellent, sitting just off a strong pace and battling on well for third behind Coolmore hopes Tentyris & Raging Force. She's far better suited out to 1400m and back against her own sex. Drawn well, she'll take a power of beating. CHATTERLEY (6) was good in the Reginald Allen last time and that form may have already been franked through Panova. Respecting her for the Waller yard despite being a maiden. TEINE AULELEI (9) had no luck last week in the Crockett Stakes, never seeing clear air. She'll have to give them a start but will be charging late. LIVE (5) is a lightly raced filly on the up. She was no match for Napoleonic last week in the G3 Red Anchor but beat the rest and that horse would've been a clear favourite if here. STARDOM (2) won the Crockett with things in her favour but will make her own luck again and should give a sight.
